<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-211-167 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 798 813</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacUser  March 1991 v7 n3 p41(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Canvas charges ahead. (Deneba Systems Inc.'s Canvas 3.0) (New onthe Menu) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ito, Russell.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Deneba Systems Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Canvas 3.0 (Computer graphics software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionGraphics Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Canvas Charges AheadandM;Following close on the heels of Illustrator 3.0 as well as of theannouncements of FreeHand 3.0 and MacDraw Pro, Canvas 3.0 now joins the ranksof significantly upgraded drawing programs.andP;  The new Canvas boasts more than50 new features, but its biggest improvements are in its text handling, theaddition of Pantone colors, enhanced Bezier curves, several new CAD features,and support for Deneba's plug-in tools first seen in UltraPaint.andP;  Canvas'text functions now include true tabs; superscripting and subscripting;fractional leading and kerning; text on a curve or shape or around anirregular object; slant margins; and character-by-character font scaling.andO;CAD features include user-definable parallel lines or curves, dashed curvesand objects, rotation around any point, and an intelligent draftingassistant.andP;  Canvas 3.0 should be available in the second quarter of 1991.andM;Deneba Software, 3305 N.W.andP;  74th Avenue, Miami, FL 33122; (305) 594-6965.andO;$395.andO;</TEXT></DOC>